contents.defaultValue:
If you exceed your sin limit, you go into sin overflow at the end of the scene. Either give up or resist.
Resistance: Roll 1d6 and add 1 for each sin mark. On a 6 or less, you pass, clearing all sin and gaining a sin mark. A result of 1 on the die always passes.
Otherwise, give up.

INSTRUCTIONS:
NAME HOOK
SLASH HOOK ONCE WHEN:

- Gaining the same hook again
- Pressure increases
- Rolling a 1 on the risk die

WHEN A HOOK FILLS UP, ERASE AND RESOLVE IT

At the end of each session, answer each question, then gain 1 xp for each 'yes.' Each time you fill your xp bar, empty it and cash an advance. +1 xp cap per additional blasphemy.

- Did you survive?
- Did you follow your first agenda item?
- Did you follow at least one bolded agenda item?
- Did you follow two or more bolded agenda items?
- Did you take an injury or affliction?

contents.rollMessage:
Risk Roll

Standard Risk: ${risk:=[1d6]}$
(1): 3 stress, (2-4): 2 stress, (5+): 1 stress

contents.value: Adjust up or down by ¬±1 depending on the situation.
Only usable on a 1 on the risk roll, once a hunt. Check sin sheet for details.

contents.defaultValue:
Add a twist to the fight. It could:

- make something hard
- deal 1 stress at the end of the round to all exorcists
- make the sin take 1 less slash under certain circumstances
- make the sin deal 1 more stress under certain circumstances
- change the parameters of the fight.

The same effect cannot stack with itself.

Complications are worse and take more effort to deal with the worse the reaction die (5+): 1 action, (2-4): 2 talisman, (1): 4 talisman. A sin can add a complication up to three times per conflict scene total.

Threaten a worse consequence, 1/round. An exorcist may immediately make an action roll to try and counter the threat.
Threats can, if executed:

- Inflict stress (1): 6 stress, (2-3): 4 stress, (4+): 2 stress
- Completely separate an exorcist
- Afflict an exorcist
- Cause collateral damage
- Massively change the parameters of the fight
